# UI component rules

## Design priorities
- clean
- readable
- trustworthy
- simple
- responsive

## Component philosophy
- Prefer reusable components when there is an actual repeat pattern
- Do not abstract too early
- Keep component APIs simple
- Prefer readability over cleverness

## Styling rules
- Preserve the current visual system unless explicitly asked to redesign it
- Make changes that improve polish without creating a new design language
- Avoid inconsistent spacing, button treatments, and typography
- Keep forms simple and easy to complete
- Ensure hover, focus, and disabled states are clear

## Responsive behavior
Every UI change should consider:
- small phones
- tablets
- desktop

Avoid:
- clipped text
- overflowing cards
- horizontal scroll
- tiny tap targets
- unreadable stacked layouts

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML where possible
- Preserve or improve keyboard accessibility
- Ensure labels exist for form controls
- Do not rely on color alone to communicate meaning
- Keep contrast strong enough for readability

## Performance
- Avoid unnecessarily large client-side components
- Prefer server-friendly patterns where appropriate
- Do not add animation or interactivity unless it improves the user experience